# AI/ML Internship – Day 1: Environment Setup & Kubernetes

## Objective

Set up the development environment for the AI/ML internship and learn the basics of working with Kubernetes-based GPU instances.

## Topics Covered

* SSH login using assigned credentials
* Basic Linux terminal commands
* Editing configuration files using `vim`
* Creating and deploying Kubernetes pods
* Managing pods and services with `kubectl`
* Accessing a running container using `kubectl exec`
* Installing JupyterLab inside the container
* Launching JupyterLab and accessing it through a web browser
* Managing the pod lifecycle by deleting resources after use

## Commands Practiced

* `vim pod-service.yaml`
* `kubectl apply -f pod-service.yaml`
* `kubectl get pods`
* `kubectl get services`
* `kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- bash`
* `pip install jupyterlab`
* `jupyter lab --NotebookApp.token="<token>"`
* `kubectl delete -f pod-service.yaml`

## Outcome

Successfully configured a Kubernetes-based GPU development environment, launched JupyterLab, and gained hands-on experience with container deployment, management, and cleanup for AI/ML workflows.
